Assists with meeting coordination, including preparing materials, setting up virtual and in-person logistics, and tracking follow-up tasks. Develops, formats, and reviews internal reports, correspondence, and presentations. Ensures compliance with records management policies for filing and document retention. Coordinates office supply procurement and inventory management. Provides first-level review of administrative workflows to enhance efficiency. Supports budgeting and invoice tracking for office-related expenses.

raw_data.title: Administrative Specialist III
raw_data.description: Provides high-level administrative support with added responsibilities in coordination, reporting, and operational assistance for leadership. Performs all duties of Administrative Specialist 2 with greater involvement in strategic administrative operations. Develops, maintains, and analyzes reports to support leadership decision-making. Assists with policy implementation related to administrative processes. Manages meeting logistics, including technical support for audiovisual needs and facilitation of conference calls or webinars. Leads or assists in planning major office events, workshops, and conferences. Serves as a liaison between internal and external stakeholders for administrative matters. Oversees procurement activities, including researching vendors, coordinating purchases, and tracking expenses. Assists in onboarding new staff by managing administrative requirements and training on office procedures.
